newsitem.title: ISRAEL: Palestinian boy killed, toll in two days at 10.
newsitem.headline: Palestinian boy killed, toll in two days at 10.

text.p: A Palestinian boy was shot dead in clashes with Israeli troops, raising to five the number of Palestinians killed in Gaza Strip violence on Thursday, health officials said.

An official at Gaza's Shifa hospital identified the dead boy as Qassem Bheisi, 16, shot in clashes at the Kfar Darom Jewish settlement. Ten Palestinians have died in two days of the bloodiest sustained violence since the return of Palestinian President Yasser Arafat to the Gaza Strip two years ago.
